> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/28/01 2:03:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=972.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Recalling some good GM experiences</span><hr size=1> I was talking with some friends and we were recalling our first days playing EQ. Some memorable events that came up... <br>
<br>
** Disclaimer: All of these events took place within the first few months of EQ going &quot;Live&quot;. GM's were perhaps given more flexibilty back then when they wern't being abused so much ** <br>
<br>
1. A GM broadcast on Tunare encouraging players to play enchanters because no one realized how cool a chanter could be. <br>
<br>
2. I once lost my body to a bug in the mino caves in Steamfont. A guide and kept us company (for like 30 minutes) until a GM came and gave me my &quot;Leg up&quot; kit. This was a genuine bug that affected many players. <br>
<br>
3. I once &quot;misplaced&quot; my body in Dragnor's Cauldron and a GM couldn't tell me where my body was because it was in a &quot;player accesible spot&quot;, but he kept giving me &quot;hints&quot;  <br>
&lt;&lt; &quot;No, cold, cold..warm, warm HOT!!&gt;&gt; <br>
<br>
4. This one is pretty cool. I was to perform a marriage ceremony in the Elven tree city but missed the boat at the FP docks. I (not knowing any better as a newbie) /petitioned and explained the situation. I got a responce from a GM in like 10 minutes and he actually tported me BB!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
5. The first Griffon being killed on Tunare and the first SG being killed. A guild known as the Stormravens organized a big hunt and slayed the first griffon in the EC tunnel. We had a GM turn out to watch (as well as tons of other folks) and cheer us on. The Stormravens went on to slay the first SG (i think) on the server too. Its funny because the event was so similar to a &quot;big raid&quot; but had much more drama surrounding it. Ahh to be a newb again  <br>
<br>
6. GM's that used to broadcast when dragons were slayed on a server for the first time. &lt;&lt;Guild &quot;so and so&quot; has slayed the mighty Vox! Three cheers for &quot;so and so&quot;!&gt;&gt; <br>
<br>
Anyways, I hope others can add &quot;happy memories&quot; to this thread. I'd luv to read them. By the way this isn't a slam against the GM's and guides. I fully understand (and sympathize) that they must follow rules themselves and must grow a thick skin to endure the constant abuse. <br>
<br>
That being said, please don't post any &quot;unhappy memories&quot;. I kinda want to keep this a positive thread. Thanks! <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umidwestpatriot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MidwestPatriot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/28/01 3:10:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=972.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Recalling some good GM experiences</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> When I first started, some one told me I needed to /Petition when I died in the well and could not find my corpse (at the secret entrance to Qeynos Catacombs outside the city).  I fell down the well (&quot;under the world&quot; they say)while swimming out, and took 10,000 points of damage.  My corpse was no where to be found. haha.<br>
<br>
I remember being so impressed by the items that the female elf GM wore who retrieved my corpse.  She was omnipotent a true goddess.  I would have died to get just one of the items she wore on her.<br>
<br>
And I still would today <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
She was friendly, mysterious, twinked, and damn hot, everything I look for in a female wood elf ) <br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
