Minuet of Qeynos <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utheycallmetasker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Theycallmetasker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/28/01 8:14:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=972.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> good GM experiences....right</span><hr size=1> I once saw a msg come up on my screen that said something like &quot;The time to respond to this request has expired&quot; Not knowing what that was, i petitioned it. The GM came back with some line that there was a GM quest in the zone and that I had missed my chance to join it and get some uber loot of somekind. Later after a few tells, he admits that it was a hoax and said &quot;well GMs have to have fun too&quot; Fun like my boot up yer sorry ass?<br>
<br>
When I was camping ragefire for the last piece of my cleric epic, It took me 2 weeks of pure frustration to get naggy killed due to the lvl cap on killing him. He finally dies and just as I finished clearing the next FGs and start my camp, the lead GM comes in and broadcasts that the zone will be repoped due to some problem at the freeti. Naggy included. I begged and pleaded with him to leave naggy down, since I had spence a huge effort to get him killed, course I got a NO reply. The very next day as I was preparing another attempt at killing Naggy, the lead GM strolls up to my guildleader and asks if he wanted naggy depoped. I later learned that the GM and my guildleader had a great time together at one of the EQ conventions.<br>
<br>
GMs are like tits on nuns. Or like a one legged man in an ass kicking contest, you pick.<br>
<br>
Sorry Quil, but my dislike of GMs knows no bounds, and If i have ever had a &quot;good&quot; experience with a GM, I sure cant remember it.<br>
<br>
Tasker, lvl 40 Iksar Curmudgeon<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/28/01 8:19:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=972.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tons of good GM experiences ..</span><hr size=1> .. in fact, only good ones.  My favorite was the old-time &quot;surname&quot; ceremony.  Waay back there used to be no /surname command.  You had to ask a GM.  In the very early days, the GMs would actually do a naming ceremony.  The one I remember best was when the GM turned into a giant werewolf when the moon rose.  That was fun!<br>
<br>
Tunare Stormravens?  Can you shout, &quot;Spooooon!&quot;? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kendrikfv>kendrik fv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/28/01 9:03:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=972.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> GM experience</span><hr size=1> My favorite GM experience. I think it was on the LT server. I was playing my enchanter and needed to buy some gems to fill an order. Unfortunately, the npc in the guild in Freeport was standing at the door instead of her usual spawn point further inside. When hailed, she replied she was busy so I /petitioned the problem. Not long after that, the GM shows up, a high elven lass in armor wielding a wicked looking sword. She said she had to kill the NPC to get it to repop and proceeded to attack it. The NPC gave the usual &quot;High Elves like you need to be dead&quot; message and killed the GM in 3 hits. I stood there stunned and sent the GM a tell asking what the hell just happened. She replied &quot;hehe, forgot to turn on invulnerability :P&quot;. I took a few screen shots of her corpse and sent them to the server's website for laughs. Lesson learned; GM's are human too. <br>
<br>
I have had nothing but good interactions with GM's, though I have seen more than my share of other's copping an attitude with the GM when they appeared and the GM getting annoyed. Personally, if you act like a spoiled ass, you should be treated like one. GM's have way more patience than I do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=morgrist>Morgrist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/28/01 10:27:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=972.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Far as FV is concerned....</span><hr size=1> GM's and guides alike have been reasonable and prompt as possible in answering petitions.<br>
 <br>
Mostly,I sic them on really bad names (TM).<br>
 <br>
-Morgrist Vanadil (League of Shadows)<br>
