<br>
Man I can remember the good old days, when everyone thought that agil and dex was waaay better then +AC. Serp bracers were so cool! Heh, warriors could get to 3k hps when fully buffed and that was soooo uber!! Remember when fear first opened and lvl 1 ogres would swarm in to take a look? Think I was lvl 40 when I went on my first raid there. LOL and when you died on the raid, you only got a revive cuz it was so hairy that the raid leaders (/rude charon) didnt want the clerics too low on mana? First time I saw some druid floating above the ground I was just floored :P Ahhh sweet memories<br>
<br>
Tasker <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/29/01 12:41:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=972.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SR...?</span><hr size=1> I, like Tasker have had nothing but bad GM experiences so I rather dislike them.  For the job I see them do, I don't know why we even have some except for cases involving bugs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uquillionthegnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quillion the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/29/01 1:57:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=972.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SR...?</span><hr size=1> Well, GM's used to be much more friendly and had alot less rules. Then as the game grew the GM's started to get alot of abuse and some players even learned how to trick GM's into doing things for them.<br>
<br>
Some GM's did not react so well to this. There were even a few instances of GM's abusing there powers. So, a set of guidelines was created for the GM's to follow and today most of them pretty much stick to those guidelines.<br>
<br>
